description: The Skinwalker team is back! For every action there's an equal reaction. Rey's a good kid who's made some mistakes. Noah's an ex-cop who became a bondsmen in a failed attempt to save his marriage. One choice is about to send both their lives into chaos.
name: Family Values

description: Rey Quintana shouldn't be on the run. He should be at school, not on the road trying to avoid prison. Noah Conway shouldn't be after him. He should be home with his daughter. Instead he's chasing this bail-jumper halfway across the state. But is this jaded hunter ready for his prey?
name: Needles

description: Noah is closing in on the bail-jumping Rey, but when the good-at-heart kid lets his good- for-nothing friend get in the middle, things go from bad to worse. Now Rey is on the run again, but if they were tracked down once, is it inevitable that they'll be caught again?
name: Crossroads

description: Rey stepped over the line of the law, but what first appeared to be a small shuffle has turned into a 50-yard dash. Now Rey has to decide what price he's willing to pay for his freedom while Noah, his bail-bondsman, has to catch someone with nothing left to lose.
name: Just Cause

description: Rey Quintana's mistakes have finally caught up with him in the form of bail enforcement agent Noah Conway. Even though the two men know that what's right and the law don't always match up, both are stuck playing out their part in this tragedy to the bitter end.
name: Blame

description: "Robocop" was one of the truly great bits of movie and pop-culture magic from the 1980s, and Frank Miller wanted to deliver a masterpiece with his original movie script, but Hollywood massively edited his work. In full-on action, the "Robocop" story is told as Frank Miller always intended, composed straight from the master's original writings and scripts! The vast majority of Miller's insane ideas, vicious black humor and robotic mayhem never made it to the screen, but every last bit is finally unleashed in this series! With sequential adaptation from Steven Grant and art by superstar Juan Jose Ryp, this sci-fi epic is not to be missed!
name: TPB

description:
A precious fossil is stolen from the Nacrene Museum. Can Black track it down by...following its tracks ?! Then, mysterious Team Plasma gets a step closer to finding a Legendary Pokémon!

And what is the secret power of the dark stone...?

Plus, meet Whirlipede, Trubbish, Cinccino, and many more new Pokémon of the fascinating Unova region!

Chapter Titles

  • Adventure 14: Defeating Stoutland
  • Adventure 15: The Mystery of the Missing Fossil
  • Adventure 16: A Direct Attack and a Daunting Defense
  • Adventure 17: Lost in the Big City
name: Vol. 5

description: You should've been nicer to your toys! The Teddy Scares, zombie teddies risen from the grave, make their graphic novel debut! Based on the popular toy line, Teddy Scares Volume 1 features work from Image artist Ben Roman, and SLG/Tokyopop artist Drew Rausch.
name: Wannabe

description:
Those undead troublemaking teddies are back in Teddy Scares Volume 2! Image artist Chris Moreno joins Ben Roman in this terrifying, tragic, and hilarious installment. The Teddy Scares return with five new stories of betrayal, wrath and new ways to pick on Cyrus.

Teddy Scares Volume 2 features Redmond, Hester, Edwin, Cyrus, the tragic origins of Rita Mortis and the introduction of the terrifying, Teddy Bear eating, Rasputin!

Stories

  1. Just One of the Bears
  2. Rasputin Part One
  3. Winston
  4. Rasputin Part Two
  5. Cherished Memories
  6. Why I'm Mean

From the bowels of hell to your bookshelf! The Teddy Scares return in an all new, sad, viciously humorous volume. Image artist Rob Guillory joins the twisted art team, headed by Christine Larsen.

The "Five Teddy Bears of the Apocalypse" return to wreak havoc and destruction in Teddy Scares Volume 3.

This dark, deviant tome features all your favorite bears in five new stories inclucing the heartbreaking oriign of Edwin Morose, the creation of Cyrus' even stupider alter ego, Super Cyrus, the end of one bear at the jaws of the vicious Rasputin and the arrival of Eli Wretch!

Stories

  • Collector's Item
  • Rasputin Part Three
  • Super Cyrus
  • Rasputin Part Four
  • My Abigail

The 'Five Teddy Bears of the Apocalypse' return to wreak havoc and destruction in the Season 1 finale of Teddy Scares! Christine Larsen and SLG/Tokyopop artist Drew Rausch head up a stellar group of talent in this latest volume featuring a flashback of Redmond Gore's arrival at the dump and the tragic secret of Hester Golem beautifully realized by Marvel/Image artist Chris Moreno!
